Title: Noncommutative geometry and quantization
Authors: Joseph C. Varilly
Comments: 26 pages, standard Latex, needs XyPic fonts. Lectures delivered at
  the X Jorge Andre Swieca Summer School on Particles and Fields, Sao Paulo,
  7-12 February 1999
Report-no: UCR-CIMM-6-99
\\
  We examine some recent developments in noncommutative geometry, including
spin geometries on noncommutative tori and their quantization by the
Shale-Stinespring procedure, as well as the emergence of Hopf algebras as a
tool linking index theory and renormalization calculations
